review_comments.body:
Maybe a `try` - `finally` block is more robust here? Just in case some strange exception comes out from `doHandleDelivery()`... I suggest the following snippet:

``` Java
try {
    doHandleDelivery(consumerTag, envelope, properties, body);
} finally {
    if (!consumer.getEndpoint().isAutoAck()) {
        lock.release();
    }
}
```

